    "content": "<p>8\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 8th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>Since a long time systemd has had the ConditionHost= unit file setting, which allows limiting execution of a unit to a specific host. As argument it takes either a hostname (with shell-style globbing, nicely aligning with the question mark logic in /etc/hostname, as in the 5th episode of this season of this series), or a machine ID (i.e. /etc/machine-id) specification.</p>",
