      "content": "<p>This is useful as you can ship a single configuration for a fleet of devices, but still have some of it be specific to a subset (or exclude a subset) of the whole fleet. (In fact, by combining the question mark stuff with the glob matching you can even execute services on a randomized subset of your fleet this way\u2026)</p><p>With v258 we are slightly extending ConditionHost= a bit. In addition to matching against the two aforementioned host identifiers, \u2026</p>",
