      "replies_count": 0,
      "reblogs_count": 0,
      "favourites_count": 12,
      "quotes_count": 0,
      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p>\u2026 the setting may now also match against the boot ID (i.e /proc/sys/kernel/random/boot_id) and the product ID of the hardware (i.e. `run0 varlinkctl call /run/systemd/io.systemd.Hostname io.systemd.Hostname.Describe &#39;&#39; | jq -r .ProductUUID`).</p><p>The former is useful as it means you can deploy configuration that will only apply to a certain *state* of the system, while the latter might be useful if your inventory tracks hardware instead of OS installations.</p>",
